In December 2022, the company retired $329 million principal amount of our 2.40 percent Notes at the natural maturity
date. In May 2022, we redeemed $1,250 million principal amount of our 4.95 percent Notes due 2026. We paid
premiums above face value of $79 million to redeem the debt and recognized a loss on debt extinguishment of $83
million which is included in the "Other expenses" line on our consolidated income statement. We also paid $500 million
to retire the outstanding principal amount of the floating rate notes due 2022 at maturity.
In the first quarter of 2022, we completed a debt refinancing consisting of three concurrent transactions: a tender offer
to repurchase existing debt for cash; exchange offers to retire certain debt in exchange for new debt and cash; and a
new debt issuance to partially fund the cash paid in the tender and exchange offers.
