On January 15, 2021, we assumed financial derivative instruments consisting of oil and natural gas swaps in
connection with the acquisition of Concho. At the acquisition date, these financial derivative instruments acquired were
recognized at fair value as a net liability of $456 million with settlement dates under the contracts through December
31, 2022. During 2021, we recognized a loss on settlement of these derivatives contracts of $305 million. This loss is
recorded within the “Sales and other operating revenues” line on our consolidated income statement. In connection with
the settlement, we issued a cash payment of $761 million during 2021 which is included within “Cash Flows From
Operating Activities” on our consolidated statement of cash flows.
